---
import PageLayout from "../layouts/PageLayout.astro";
import Section from "../components/Section.astro";
import Button from "../components/Button.astro";
import { siteConfig } from "../data/site-config";
---

<PageLayout
  title="About GADI"
  description="GADI is an international interdisciplinary research network studying the common principles of generalization across biological and artificial learning systems."
  pageTitle="About"
  pageSubtitle="Bridging the science of generalization"
>
  <!-- ─── Mission ───────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <Section background="white">
    <div class="fade-up">
      <p class="label-caps mb-3 text-indigo-600">Our Mission</p>
      <h2 class="font-display text-4xl font-semibold text-ink-900 lg:text-5xl">
        A unified science of how learning transfers
      </h2>
      <div class="mt-5 h-px w-12 bg-gradient-to-r from-indigo-500 to-transparent" />
      <p class="mt-8 max-w-prose text-lg font-body leading-relaxed text-stone-700">
        Learning systems, from humans and animals to artificial neural networks, must apply past
        experience to situations they have never encountered before. This capacity, variously called
        generalization, transfer of learning, or extrapolation, is fundamental to adaptive behavior,
        robust intelligence, and effective education.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-5 max-w-prose space-y-5 text-base font-body leading-relaxed text-stone-600">
        <p>
          Despite its centrality, generalization remains poorly understood at a fundamental level.
          Research on this problem is distributed across scientific domains that use incompatible
          terminology, divergent experimental paradigms, and incommensurable theoretical frameworks.
          Progress has been slowed by the very structure of academic disciplines.
        </p>
        <p>
          GADI was established to build the infrastructure (the communication channels, the
          collaborative opportunities, and the shared conceptual language) necessary to connect
          these fragmented communities and accelerate progress toward unified principles of
          generalization.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <!-- ─── The research problem ─────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <Section label="Scientific Context" background="cream">
    <div class="fade-up">
      <h2 class="font-display text-4xl font-semibold text-ink-900 lg:text-5xl">
        The generalization problem
      </h2>
      <div class="mt-5 h-px w-12 bg-gradient-to-r from-indigo-500 to-transparent" />
      <p class="mt-6 max-w-prose text-base font-body leading-relaxed text-stone-700">
        Each field has developed deep expertise on a facet of generalization. Yet the terminology
        rarely crosses disciplinary lines: "stimulus generalization" in psychology,
        "out-of-distribution generalization" in AI, and "transfer of training" in education refer
        to related, perhaps identical, phenomena studied in near-complete isolation. GADI creates
        the conditions for these communities to find common ground.
      </p>
    </div>

    <dl class="mt-12 divide-y divide-cream-300 stagger-children">
      {[
        {
          discipline: "Psychology",
          insight: "Studies how humans learn categories, transfer knowledge, and generalize across contexts, using controlled experimental paradigms to isolate the mechanisms underlying these processes.",
        },
        {
          discipline: "Neuroscience",
          insight: "Investigates the neural substrates of generalization, including how the brain encodes, abstracts, and transfers learned information to novel contexts.",
        },
        {
          discipline: "Artificial Intelligence",
          insight: "Develops models that generalize from training data to novel inputs, including out-of-distribution generalization, few-shot learning, and transfer learning in neural networks.",
        },
        {
          discipline: "Education",
          insight: "Studies how skills and knowledge transfer across tasks and contexts, and how instructional design can promote robust and flexible generalization in students.",
        },
        {
          discipline: "Linguistics",
          insight: "Examines how speakers generalize grammatical patterns, lexical categories, and phonological regularities from the input they receive to novel utterances.",
        },
        {
          discipline: "Psychiatry",
          insight: "Investigates maladaptive generalization, where learned responses extend inappropriately to safe contexts, as a clinically significant failure mode of adaptive learning.",
        },
      ].map((item) => (
        <div class="grid gap-3 py-6 md:grid-cols-[180px_1fr] md:gap-12">
          <dt class="label-caps text-indigo-600 md:pt-0.5">{item.discipline}</dt>
          <dd class="text-sm font-body leading-relaxed text-stone-700">{item.insight}</dd>
        </div>
      ))}
    </dl>
  </Section>

  <!-- ─── Objectives ────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <Section label="What We Do" background="white">
    <div class="mb-12 fade-up">
      <h2 class="font-display text-4xl font-semibold text-ink-900 lg:text-5xl">
        Five objectives
      </h2>
      <div class="mt-5 h-px w-12 bg-gradient-to-r from-indigo-500 to-transparent" />
    </div>
    <div class="divide-y divide-cream-200 border border-cream-200">
      {siteConfig.objectives.map((obj, i) => (
        <div class="grid gap-4 px-8 py-8 fade-up md:grid-cols-[80px_1fr] md:gap-10">
          <div class="font-display text-4xl font-bold text-indigo-200 leading-none select-none">
            {obj.number}
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-semibold text-ink-900">{obj.title}</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm font-body leading-relaxed text-stone-600">{obj.description}</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </Section>

</PageLayout>
